31:43.985 --> 31:45.976
They're so red,

31:46.054 --> 31:47.988
and ripe

31:48.056 --> 31:49.853
and luscious.

31:49.924 --> 31:52.085
So sullen.

31:52.160 --> 31:54.822
Brutal.

31:54.896 --> 31:58.059
- Let's see what you'd look like with lipstick.
- I should go.

31:58.132 --> 32:01.533
- You'd make such a pretty girl.
- Ignore her, Matthew.

32:01.603 --> 32:08.202
- She sucks in all the air around her.
- I really have to be getting back to my hotel.

32:08.276 --> 32:12.042
No. Why?
We were going to invite you to stay.

32:12.113 --> 32:13.944
- Really?
- Sure.

32:14.015 --> 32:17.314
Our parents are going to be
in Trouville for a month.

32:17.385 --> 32:21.344
We thought you might like
to move your things here.

32:21.422 --> 32:23.788
- Really?
- Sure.

32:23.858 --> 32:27.521
But you just met me two days ago.
You barely even know me.

32:27.595 --> 32:30.428
This way we get to know you.
Do you have to stay in the hotel?

32:30.498 --> 32:35.026
- No.
- We'll go and pick up what you need. OK?

32:35.103 --> 32:37.264
Come on.

32:37.338 --> 32:39.829
What about you?

32:42.310 --> 32:44.073
It was my idea.

32:45.480 --> 32:48.074
You're scaring me right now.

32:49.250 --> 32:51.445
Jesus.

32:51.619 --> 32:53.610
Jesus.

32:56.791 --> 32:59.487
I'm going to check out
the Cinémathèque, just in case.

32:59.560 --> 33:01.653
- OK.
- Don't take too long.

33:01.729 --> 33:07.065
- Don't worry. I won't. I don't have much stuff.
- With us, you're not going to need much.

33:13.174 --> 33:16.405
Just don't forget your toothbrush.

33:28.189 --> 33:33.286
Dear Mom, I guess you're surprised to be
hearing from me so soon after my last letter,

33:33.361 --> 33:38.355
but I've just moved into an apartment
belonging to a famous French author.

33:38.433 --> 33:41.800
His children are the same age as me
and have the same interests.

33:41.869 --> 33:46.431
I know how pleased you'll be to hear
I'm getting in with the right kind of people.

33:46.507 --> 33:49.442
Say hello to Father.
I hope he's not still mad at me...

33:49.744 --> 33:52.042
Listen to this, Matthew.

33:52.113 --> 33:57.312
"The difference between Keaton and Chaplin
is the difference between prose and poetry,

33:57.385 --> 34:02.322
between the aristocrat and the tramp,
between eccentricity and mysticism,

34:02.390 --> 34:06.884
between man as a machine
and man as angel".

34:06.961 --> 34:08.326
Not bad, huh?

34:08.396 --> 34:11.991
That's good. Except, for me,
there's no comparison.

34:12.533 --> 34:16.025
Why? Because Chaplin's incomparable?

34:17.905 --> 34:21.306
No. Because Keaton is incomparable.

34:22.210 --> 34:25.577
Keaton? You think Keaton's
greater than Chaplin?

34:25.646 --> 34:27.705
- Absolutely, I do.
- You're not serious.

34:27.782 --> 34:30.080
- Course I am.
- You're crazy.

34:30.150 --> 34:33.848
Come on. You can't deny
that Keaton's funnier than Chaplin.

34:33.920 --> 34:38.255
- Yes, I can.
- You don't find Keaton funnier than Chaplin?

34:38.326 --> 34:40.590
I don't think anyone's funnier than Chaplin.

34:40.661 --> 34:43.425
Keaton is. Even when he's
not doing anything he's funny.

34:43.498 --> 34:46.433
And he looks like Godard.
Keaton is a real filmmaker.

34:46.501 --> 34:50.369
Chaplin - all he cares about
is his own performance, his own ego.

34:50.438 --> 34:52.303
- Bullshit.
- It's not bullshit.

34:52.373 --> 34:57.333
Yes, it is. Sometimes I think you Americans
understand fuck all about your own culture.

34:57.411 --> 35:02.212
- No wonder you never got Jerry Lewis.
- Don't even get me started on Jerry Lewis.

35:02.283 --> 35:06.447
Listen, Matthew. When Chaplin wanted
to have a beautiful shot, he knew how.

35:06.521 --> 35:09.718
Better than Keaton. Better than anybody.

35:09.791 --> 35:12.089
<i>You remember the last shot of City Lights?</i>

35:12.160 --> 35:16.153
He looks at the flower girl, she looks at him.

35:16.764 --> 35:21.133
And don't forget she's been blind,
so she was seeing him for the very first time.

35:21.202 --> 35:25.536
And it's as if, through her eyes,
we also see him for the very first time.

35:25.606 --> 35:29.007
Charlie Chaplin, Charlot,
the most famous man in the world,

35:29.076 --> 35:32.944
and it's as if
we've never really seen him before.

35:38.619 --> 35:42.715
Isa, if you play that fucking record again,
I'll break it in two. OK?

35:42.790 --> 35:45.384
But you like Janis Joplin.

35:47.628 --> 35:49.061
Stop it.

35:49.130 --> 35:51.826
I said stop it, Isabelle.

35:52.633 --> 35:53.861
Stop!

35:53.935 --> 35:56.802
- Matthew, tell me - what film?
- What?

35:56.871 --> 36:01.535
Name a film where someone tap-dancing
drives someone else crazy.

36:01.609 --> 36:03.770
- I know this.
- Forfeit if you can't answer.

36:03.845 --> 36:07.281
<i>- Quick, quick or you'll pay the forfeit.
- Top Hat. Top Hat.</i>

36:07.348 --> 36:11.375
Fred Astaire is dancing
over Ginger Rogers' room.

36:13.588 --> 36:16.580
And she's mad because he wakes her up.

36:22.530 --> 36:24.327
I'm right.

36:25.766 --> 36:26.892
He's good.

36:26.968 --> 36:29.698
You thinking what I'm thinking?

36:29.770 --> 36:31.203
What?

36:31.272 --> 36:32.864
<i>Bande à part.</i>

36:32.940 --> 36:34.931
You're right.

36:35.142 --> 36:38.407
Why are you two looking at me like that?

36:38.479 --> 36:40.276
Well,

36:40.348 --> 36:42.714
you see, my little Matthew,

36:42.783 --> 36:46.082
there's something Theo and I
have been meaning to do for a long time,

36:46.153 --> 36:49.020
but we've been waiting
for the right person to do it with.

36:49.090 --> 36:51.718
- And I think you're finally it.
- To do what?

36:51.792 --> 36:55.091
<i>- Try to beat the record of Bande à part.
- What record?</i>

36:55.162 --> 36:57.221
<i>- You've seen Bande à part?
- Yeah.</i>

36:57.298 --> 37:01.291
- Where they race through the Louvre?
- Remind me.

37:01.369 --> 37:04.133
To beat the world record
of nine minutes and 45 seconds.

37:04.205 --> 37:07.766
- Oh, yeah. Of course.
- We're going to beat their record.

37:11.212 --> 37:14.204
- What?
- What's the matter?

37:14.615 --> 37:17.345
- Nothing, really.
- Not afraid, are you?

37:17.418 --> 37:21.013
- No. I'm not afraid.
- What, then?

37:21.088 --> 37:24.854
It's easy for you two. I'm an American,
what you French call an "alien".

37:24.926 --> 37:28.157
- So?
- So if I get caught, I get deported.

37:28.229 --> 37:31.426
Don't worry, little man.
We're not going to get caught.

37:31.499 --> 37:34.229
<i>- You don't know that.
- They weren't caught in Bande à part.</i>

37:34.302 --> 37:37.328
- If we beat the record, we won't be caught.
- It's a movie.

37:37.405 --> 37:39.566
Go get Papa's stopwatch. Come on.

37:39.640 --> 37:44.543
- It's a great idea...
- Matthew, this is a test.

37:44.612 --> 37:48.275
Are you going to pass it or fail it?

37:48.349 --> 37:50.112
Be careful.

37:50.184 --> 37:52.914
A lot depends on how you answer.

38:26.087 --> 38:31.115
Nine minutes and 28 seconds.
We beat the record by 17 seconds.

38:33.327 --> 38:36.194
Matthew. My little Matthew.

38:36.263 --> 38:38.754
You were wonderful.

38:42.837 --> 38:45.067
We accept him. One of us.

38:45.239 --> 38:48.436
We accept him. One of us.

38:48.509 --> 38:51.808
One of us. We accept her, we accept her.

38:55.983 --> 38:57.780
We accept him. One of us.

38:57.852 --> 38:58.944
One of us.

39:45.466 --> 39:51.427
We accept you. One of us.
One of us. One of us. One of us. One of us.

39:57.344 --> 39:59.335
That's Mother.

40:01.315 --> 40:03.476
I'm too wet to answer.

40:07.755 --> 40:10.690
Isa's smart, but she doesn't know
how to deal with parents.

40:10.758 --> 40:15.058
- What do you mean?
- I mean, it's not enough to ignore them.

40:15.129 --> 40:19.896
They should all be arrested. Put on trial.

40:19.967 --> 40:22.299
Confess their crimes.

40:22.369 --> 40:28.001
Sent to the country
for self-criticism and re-education.

40:29.243 --> 40:33.873
- They're already in the country.
- They are at the seaside.

40:33.948 --> 40:35.939
That's different.

40:41.589 --> 40:42.954
Too bad.

40:43.023 --> 40:45.583
My parents never go anywhere.

40:45.659 --> 40:49.026
At least you have the house to yourselves.

40:51.098 --> 40:53.623
Where are you going?

40:54.635 --> 41:00.505
- I gotta get out of these clothes.
- It'll be cold in your room. Come into mine.

41:27.935 --> 41:30.836
You can wear this.

41:31.972 --> 41:34.202
Thanks.

41:52.660 --> 41:54.719
I'm going to get a Coca.

41:54.795 --> 41:57.286
- Want one?
- OK.

42:47.214 --> 42:51.514
- Could you open the door? My hands are full.
- Just a second.

42:54.321 --> 42:56.755
- Why didn't you open the door?
- I was...

42:56.824 --> 42:59.156
I was dressing.

43:16.644 --> 43:19.579
What film?

43:25.619 --> 43:28.679
In what film does a chorus line dance like this

43:28.756 --> 43:32.385
with a singer in a fur coat?

43:32.459 --> 43:35.087
- I've seen this film?
- We saw it together.

43:35.162 --> 43:37.255
We did? Give me a clue.

43:37.331 --> 43:40.323
- Certainly not.
- Come on. Be a sport. The director's name.

43:40.401 --> 43:42.266
No.

43:43.304 --> 43:47.035
- Number of words in the title?
- I said no.

43:47.975 --> 43:50.136
The first letter of the first word.

43:50.210 --> 43:52.508
God. You're pathetic.

43:52.579 --> 43:55.605
Isn't he pathetic?
Don't you think he's pathetic?

43:55.683 --> 43:59.847
- Matthew, I bet you know.
- Don't you dare help him.

43:59.920 --> 44:02.684
Did the Sphinx give Oedipus a clue?

44:02.756 --> 44:04.917
Fuck you.

44:06.193 --> 44:08.218
Give up?

44:20.441 --> 44:21.738
<i>Blonde Venus.</i>

44:21.809 --> 44:22.434
Shit...

44:22.509 --> 44:25.137
Marlene Dietrich. 1932.

44:25.212 --> 44:27.874
I knew that.

44:29.016 --> 44:32.474
- Forfeit.
- If you insist.

44:32.553 --> 44:35.113
I dare you to do now,

44:35.189 --> 44:40.752
in front of us,
what I have watched you do in front of her.

44:40.828 --> 44:42.591
Who?

44:42.663 --> 44:47.691
- I don't know what you're talking about.
- Oh, yes, you do, my pet.

44:47.768 --> 44:49.167
Forfeit.

44:50.537 --> 44:54.371
What a bitch you are. A bitch and a sadist.

44:54.441 --> 44:57.842
Are you going to pay the forfeit or not?

45:04.051 --> 45:06.212
Very well.

45:14.928 --> 45:20.264
I want you to do it the way you did it
when you thought no one was watching.

47:06.907 --> 47:10.866
Let's have a drink. I'll meet you downstairs.

47:45.279 --> 47:50.080
Why won't you admit you were thrilled?
Come on, you can tell me.

47:51.752 --> 47:53.014
What?

47:53.086 --> 47:56.886
- Weren't you just a tiny bit excited?
- What is it you're trying to get me to say?

47:56.957 --> 47:59.653
Nothing. I asked you a question.

47:59.726 --> 48:03.059
- I suppose you know who you sound like.
- Who?

48:03.130 --> 48:05.963
- Isabelle.
- Why not? She's my twin sister.

48:06.033 --> 48:09.901
- You two are twins?
- Yes. She'd be me if she were a man.

48:09.970 --> 48:15.203
- That's crap. You're not identical.
- Yes, we are. We're Siamese twins.

48:15.275 --> 48:17.300
Joined here.

48:20.547 --> 48:22.742
You're a strange one, Theo.

48:22.816 --> 48:28.049
Half an hour ago, I saw you look at her
as though you wanted to strangle her.

48:28.121 --> 48:30.282
I did.

48:30.357 --> 48:33.520
- I don't understand you.
- Don't you have brothers or sisters?

48:33.594 --> 48:37.325
- I have two older sisters.
- Didn't you ever want to strangle them?

48:37.397 --> 48:41.800
Course I did, but I never masturbated
in front of them, and I never...

48:41.868 --> 48:45.668
They never forced me
to do anything I never wanted to do.

48:47.274 --> 48:50.243
You think Isabelle forced me, do you?

49:01.421 --> 49:05.357
Deep down,
I knew things couldn't go on as before.

49:05.425 --> 49:08.451
Now the stakes had been raised.

49:08.528 --> 49:14.160
But, for a while at least, there did seem to be
a kind of truce between Theo and Isabelle.

49:14.234 --> 49:17.499
And then, one evening...

49:32.319 --> 49:35.482
- What film?
- What film?

49:35.555 --> 49:40.424
Name the film where a cross
marks the spot of a murder or pay the forfeit.

49:43.363 --> 49:46.355
- You too, Matthew.
- Me?

49:46.433 --> 49:49.493
What have I done?

49:49.569 --> 49:52.299
Name the film or pay the forfeit.

49:56.677 --> 50:00.670
- Time's up.
- Time's up? You didn't give me a chance.

50:00.747 --> 50:04.308
<i>- The film?
- Scarface. Howard Hawks.</i>

50:04.384 --> 50:06.875
1932.

50:06.953 --> 50:09.183
And the forfeit?

50:10.190 --> 50:11.680
Well,

50:15.262 --> 50:18.060
as you know, Isabelle, I'm not a sadist.

50:18.131 --> 50:22.295
I just want to see everyone happy.
No one left out.

50:22.369 --> 50:23.700
So,

50:23.770 --> 50:26.136
I'd like you

50:27.140 --> 50:29.700
and Matthew

50:29.776 --> 50:32.244
to make love in front of me.

50:32.312 --> 50:37.045
But not in here. I don't fancy sleeping
in someone else's revolting spunk.

50:37.117 --> 50:40.883
- No offence, Matthew.
- Where?

50:40.954 --> 50:45.550
In the spare room. In front of the Delacroix.

50:45.625 --> 50:49.493
Maybe one reproduction will inspire another.

50:49.563 --> 50:51.929
- I won't do it.
- You won't do it?

50:51.998 --> 50:55.161
- You wouldn't.
- Matthew isn't my type.

52:04.471 --> 52:07.872
I need to go to the bathroom.

53:02.729 --> 53:04.720
This is silly.

53:04.798 --> 53:07.289
Come out of there.

53:19.646 --> 53:21.136
OK. All right.

53:21.214 --> 53:22.806
- Look...
- Too late.

53:22.883 --> 53:27.946
You're hurting me. I don't...
I'm not violent. I'm against violence.

53:28.021 --> 53:31.957
- I'm not gonna resist - look.
- So shut up.

53:33.293 --> 53:37.730
You know, Matthew,
you aren't being very gallant.

53:37.797 --> 53:41.563
Is the prospect
of making love to me so hateful?

53:43.637 --> 53:47.334
I've seen you. I saw you in bed together.

53:48.341 --> 53:51.367
Our guest has been spying on us.

53:51.444 --> 53:54.572
Now, that wasn't
a friendly thing to do, Matthew.

53:54.648 --> 53:58.140
Especially when we've been so hospitable.

54:02.088 --> 54:04.556
I'm not resisting.

54:20.840 --> 54:25.834
How sweet of you, Matthew,
to keep my image next to your heart.

54:25.912 --> 54:28.107
I didn't...

54:36.256 --> 54:38.554
Come on. Wake up.

54:39.559 --> 54:41.049
Come on. Wake up.

54:43.061 --> 54:44.585
Isabelle?

54:44.663 --> 54:47.154
No. I'm Theo.

54:49.334 --> 54:51.495
Where is Isabelle?

55:34.379 --> 55:37.212
You have to help me.

55:57.135 --> 55:58.796
Sorry.

59:50.768 --> 59:53.259
That was the best one.

59:55.273 --> 59:58.003
What about yesterday?

59:58.910 --> 01:00:01.344
In Papa's study.

01:00:01.412 --> 01:00:04.939
You thought that was better?

01:00:05.016 --> 01:00:07.280
Please, please, please, please.

01:00:07.352 --> 01:00:10.014
- What?
- Stay inside.

01:00:12.190 --> 01:00:13.680
Matthew.

01:00:14.659 --> 01:00:17.093
My love.

01:00:17.162 --> 01:00:19.562
My first love.

01:00:20.465 --> 01:00:22.933
My great love.

01:00:23.001 --> 01:00:25.060
My great lover.

01:00:26.070 --> 01:00:28.868
My Valentino.

01:00:28.940 --> 01:00:33.900
My funny Valentino

01:01:01.606 --> 01:01:05.098
You know, I thought you had many lovers.

01:01:07.478 --> 01:01:09.810
When I first saw you at the Cinémathèque -

01:01:09.881 --> 01:01:12.509
you and Theo -

01:01:12.584 --> 01:01:15.314
you looked so cool.

01:01:16.354 --> 01:01:18.879
So sophisticated.

01:01:19.891 --> 01:01:22.189
Like a movie star.

01:01:22.260 --> 01:01:24.626
I was.

01:01:24.696 --> 01:01:26.994
I was acting, Matthew.

01:01:32.503 --> 01:01:34.835
How did you and...

01:01:35.840 --> 01:01:38.832
How did you and Theo...

01:01:38.910 --> 01:01:42.073
come together the way that you are?

01:01:42.146 --> 01:01:44.273
Theo and me?

01:01:45.083 --> 01:01:47.483
It was love at first sight.

01:01:59.664 --> 01:02:02.098
But he's never been inside you?

01:02:02.900 --> 01:02:05.198
He's always inside me.

01:02:10.074 --> 01:02:12.736
What would you do...

01:02:15.013 --> 01:02:18.449
What would you do
if your parents found out?

01:02:18.516 --> 01:02:22.680
- It must never happen.
- Yeah, I know, but...

01:02:24.789 --> 01:02:27.349
what if it did?

01:02:28.559 --> 01:02:31.084
It must never, never happen.

01:02:31.162 --> 01:02:34.928
I understand that,
but let's say that it did happen.

01:02:36.000 --> 01:02:38.400
What would you...

01:02:39.404 --> 01:02:42.134
What would you do?

01:02:47.312 --> 01:02:50.076
I would kill myself.

01:03:08.633 --> 01:03:13.661
- Where are you going?
- The kitchen. I have to get something to eat.

01:03:13.738 --> 01:03:15.899
Good luck.

01:03:50.007 --> 01:03:51.998
- Want some honey?
- No, thank you.

01:03:52.076 --> 01:03:54.010
- It's good.
- No.

01:03:54.078 --> 01:03:56.546
- It's really good. Try some.
- No.

01:03:56.614 --> 01:04:00.948
- Just try a little bit. It's really...
- No. Thank you.

01:04:09.627 --> 01:04:13.063
I want you to know that I'm grateful.

01:04:14.399 --> 01:04:15.957
Grateful?

01:04:17.201 --> 01:04:21.535
Remember what you told me in the café,
about you and Isabelle?

01:04:21.606 --> 01:04:23.801
You were right.

01:04:23.875 --> 01:04:27.208
You know, for me, you two are...

01:04:28.379 --> 01:04:32.213
you're like two halves of the same person.

01:04:32.283 --> 01:04:35.844
Now you've made me feel
like I'm a part of you.

01:04:37.422 --> 01:04:39.413
Both of you.

01:04:42.193 --> 01:04:44.855
Let's get something straight, OK?

01:04:48.900 --> 01:04:51.266
You're a nice boy and I like you a lot,

01:04:51.335 --> 01:04:53.496
but no,

01:04:55.006 --> 01:04:58.464
it wasn't always meant to be the three of us.

01:05:02.146 --> 01:05:05.138
I told you something else, remember?

01:05:06.851 --> 01:05:09.342
That Isa and I are Siamese twins.

01:05:12.690 --> 01:05:15.022
I wasn'tjoking.

01:06:02.707 --> 01:06:04.732
What's this?

01:06:04.809 --> 01:06:08.370
That, my dear brother, is a cheese fondue

01:06:08.446 --> 01:06:12.246
accompanied by a compote
of broccoli and prunes.

01:06:12.316 --> 01:06:15.012
- And this?
- That's ratatouille.

01:06:15.620 --> 01:06:19.716
- And you expect me to eat this muck?
- You expected me to cook it.

01:06:19.790 --> 01:06:23.692
- I prefer to starve.
- You will. There's nothing else in the house.

01:06:23.761 --> 01:06:25.820
Matthew?

01:06:25.897 --> 01:06:28.388
Can I serve you?

01:06:31.235 --> 01:06:33.726
The fondue or the ratatouille?

01:06:35.640 --> 01:06:37.972
Which is which?

01:06:38.042 --> 01:06:41.068
This is fondue, and this is ratatouille.

01:06:41.145 --> 01:06:45.809
No. This is the fondue,
and this is the ratatouille.

01:06:45.883 --> 01:06:48.317
The ratatouille.

01:06:48.386 --> 01:06:49.978
Ratatouille.

01:06:57.428 --> 01:06:59.919
That's fine.

01:07:06.837 --> 01:07:10.466
